        "id": "comment_tutorial",
        "type": "nodetool.workflows.base_node.Comment",
        "data": {
          "comment": "# 📝 Prompt Template\n\nThe pattern behind most NodeTool workflows: **Input → Prompt template → LLM → Output**.\n\n- **Inputs** collect typed values (here: two strings) that the person running the app fills in.\n- **Prompt template** is a Jinja string with `{{ placeholders }}` — it separates *what varies* (the inputs) from *what stays fixed* (your instructions), so you can restyle the whole task without touching the graph.\n- **LLM** (the Agent node) reads the filled-in prompt and answers. It has no tools attached — that's what makes it a plain LLM call instead of a research agent.\n- **Output** exposes the LLM's answer to the app UI.\n\n**Try this:** change Topic and Audience, or rewrite the prompt template to ask for something else entirely (a recipe, a code review, a bedtime story) — the shape of the graph never has to change."
        },
        "ui_properties": {
          "selected": false,
          "position": {
